## 1. Concept & Vision

> *"The world ended. But people still walk. And wherever people walk together, something new grows."*

Caravan is a Bluetooth proximity game where walking near other players forges bonds between your caravans. The longer you walk in proximity, the longer your chain — and longer chains unlock shared survival bonuses neither player could achieve alone.

The game runs quietly in your pocket. No GPS. No maps. The entire world is defined by one thing: who is physically near you right now, and what they are willing to do. Every stranger is an unknown quantity — a potential chain-mate, a hostile raider, a black market trader, or a political operative moving resources across a fractured wasteland economy.

Beneath the street-level survival game sits a living macroeconomy: nations issuing currencies, syndicates running shadow ledgers, derivative markets pricing future scarcity, and political leaders who can embargo entire commodity classes — or be brought down by the syndicates they tried to suppress.

