## 3. Bluetooth Proximity Mechanic

### 3.1 Technical Approach

Caravan uses Bluetooth Low Energy (BLE) advertising and scanning — the same technology as AirDrop and COVID exposure notification. No GPS is required at any point. The game world is defined entirely by BLE proximity.

| Field | Value |
|---|---|
| Detection Range | ~10m (adjustable via signal strength threshold) |
| Min Link Time | 30 seconds continuous proximity to form a bond |
| Background Mode | BLE scanning continues when app is backgrounded (iOS & Android) |
| Battery Impact | Approx. 1–3% per hour — similar to Apple Find My |
| Privacy | No GPS ever. Device broadcasts an anonymous rotating token only. |
| Server Sync | State synced when internet available; full offline play supported |

### 3.2 Proximity Zones

| Zone | Effect |
|---|---|
| Close (0–3m) | Chain builds at 2x speed. High confidence of intentional co-presence. |
| Near (3–10m) | Chain builds at 1x speed. Standard proximity. |
| Distant (10–20m) | Chain pauses, does not decay. Grace zone for crowded spaces. |

### 3.3 Anti-Gaming

- Chains only build when at least one device registers motion via accelerometer
- Same device pair caps at 90 minutes of chain-building per day
- Stationary proximity in same cell for >5 minutes enters base camp mode, pausing chain growth

