## 10. Survivor System

### 10.1 Roles

| Role | Passive Contribution |
|---|---|
| Scout | Detects hostile intent signals earlier; extends BLE awareness radius +2m; improves chain range |
| Medic | Reduces survivor injury duration; remotely heals chain members' injured survivors |
| Engineer | Boosts camp upgrade speed; reduces Fuel consumption; accelerates market escrow release |
| Cook | Stretches food reserves; morale-boosting meals; buffs recovery after death |
| Guard | Reduces raid damage; improves Shield Wall; chance to intercept loot grab during 60s window |

### 10.2 Acquisition

- Reaching chain length milestones for the first time
- Purchasing survivor Blueprints on the market and constructing at camp
- Completing chain-based quests with other players

### 10.3 Permadeath

Individual survivors can be injured or permanently killed in raids. A dead survivor is memorialised. If all survivors are killed, the player resets to level 1 — but Reputation, Infamy, camp structures, and Cipher balance are preserved.

