## 11. Reputation & Infamy

> *Reputation and Infamy are the only statistics that survive death. They are the game's long-term identity system — more durable than level, more meaningful than equipment.*

### 11.1 Reputation

Reputation is built by:

- Completing trades without defaulting
- Forming and maintaining long chains with other players
- Healing or aiding chain members
- Passive accumulation while active and not attacking human players or friendly NPCs

Reputation never increases from combat. A player with high Reputation and zero kills has a higher Reputation ceiling than an equally experienced Raider. Reputation decays slowly with inactivity — approximately 10% per 30 real-world days offline.

### 11.2 Infamy

Infamy is built by:

- Successful raids on human players
- High-value kills (level gap, loot value dropped)
- Controlling significant Cipher supply
- Syndicate leadership tenure

Infamy does not decay from inactivity — a notorious player is notorious indefinitely. It can be reduced by a sustained period of non-combat play, but the reduction is slow and the history is visible. The Lost Caravan log records major kill events permanently.

### 11.3 Access Thresholds

| Role | Primary Requirement | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Syndicate membership | Infamy threshold (TBD playtesting) | Join existing NPC or player syndicate |
| Syndicate founder | Higher Infamy threshold | Start a new player-owned syndicate |
| Political candidate | High Reputation, zero player kills | Eligible for election in home nation |
| Nation leader | Elected by player base | Full economic policy tools unlocked |
| NPC Syndicate leader | Not achievable by players | Permanent NPC — world fixture |

